message: Someone inputted "Alexander Du" as the mayor from 2008 to 2014 and should probably be banned for vandalism. I checked the source and confirmed it was Dean Fortin, like Lisa Helps' page says.
/* Awards and honors */ was shortlisted for the 2010 fiction Governor General's Award so said so instead of just "Governor General's Award"

substituted period (".") for comma (",") in list of neighbourhoods
removed extraneous quotation mark (") after "MP" when Trudeau's proposed changes described
removed hyphen ("-") between South and African because words obviously are associated, now reads "South African-born"

removed hyphen from "on-launch" as that would be used in an adjective form not when the order of words is perfectly descriptive in how ("on") with what it's on ("launch"). And "on-launch" feature, but the feature is available "on launch"
/* Plot */ "which he says that it is from" to "which he says is from" in first paragraph
/* 2011–13: Curiosity, mainstream success and Kiss */ switched "begun" to "began" in last paragraph as past participle was inappropriate.
/* Criticism of the Chromebook */ new section
/* Plot */ cleaned up sentence structure and punctuation for clarity and ease of reading
/* Recognition */ inserted space between period (".") and "Time"
/* Plot */ removed hyphen from "poorly-concealed" since improper to hyphenate after -ly adverbs
/* Sales and marketing */ Changed "Between" to "From" in last paragraph because "to" was used between dates and using "and" with "Between" seemed less powerful to use with dates.
typo "in availabe as a public beta" to "available as a public beta"
/* Mainstream media */ added "when" to second sentence and omitted commas to make it easier to read and understand.
/* Decline */ checked source and corrected to "RIM was one of the biggest world market share losers"
/* The Future */ noticed "God willing there will be none" in this section, went into history, copied and pasted last good-looking entry, added "s" to misspelled CEOs name
/* History */ after "In March 2012" changed "which RIM had applied for a patent for" to "for which RIM had applied for a patent" (for technical clarity)
/* Plot */ spelling change "assigment" to "assignment" and changed hyphen to a period after it.
/* Beliefs */ changed "developement" to "development". Looked this up and found the extra "e" was part of an obsolete spelling so not entirely invalid but I changed it anyways.
Changed "[[Pardus]]" to [[Pardus (operating system)|Pardus]] to avoid disambiguation page.
